3 Prediction long COVID - CSF

3.1 ROC-AUC Anaylsis long-COVID vs non-long COVID

Computing the ROC-AUC of each molecule with respect to the long-COVID character will let us know which molecule are the best predictors when considered in isolation.

list.csf <- colnames(csf[,6:ncol(csf)])

ROC_AUC_csf <- lapply(list.csf, function(x) {   
  roc <- roc(LongCOVID ~ get(x), csf)
  auc <- auc(roc) 
  cbind(AUC = auc,  
        gene = roc$call$predictor[3],  
        variables = eval(x)) 
}) 

ROC_AUC_csf1 <- do.call(rbind, ROC_AUC_csf)

3.3.1.2 confusion matrix cross-validated full model

train_and_evaluate = function( train , valid , target , params ){
  formula = paste( target , '~' , paste(params , collapse=' + '  )  )
  logit.csf <- glm(formula, data = train, 
                 family = "binomial") 

  predictedTrain <- predict(logit.csf, train, type="response")  
  optimal <- optimalCutoff( train[ ,target] , predictedTrain)[1]
  
  predictedValid <- predict(logit.csf, valid, type="response")  
  
  return( list( 'misClassError' = misClassError(valid[, target], predictedValid, threshold=optimal),
        'target'=valid[, target],
        'predicted' =predictedValid) )
}

CV_evaluate = function( data , target , params , k ){
  l = nrow(data)
  N = as.integer( l/k )
  fold = rep(1:k , N+1)[1:l]
  fold = sample(fold , l , replace = FALSE)
  
  CVR = list( 'misClassError' = c(),
        'target'=c(),
        'predicted' =c()  )
  
  for( i in 1:k ){
    valid = fold==i
    train = fold!=i

    foldR = train_and_evaluate( data[train , ] , data[valid,] , target , params )
    CVR[['misClassError']] = c(CVR[['misClassError']] , foldR[['misClassError']]) 
    CVR[['target']] = c(CVR[['target']] , foldR[['target']]) 
    CVR[['predicted']] = c(CVR[['predicted']] , foldR[['predicted']]) 
  }
  return( CVR )
}
